headline: Phillips 66 to Divest Majority Stake in European Fuel Retail Unit
summary: PSX is divesting a 65% stake in its Germany and Austria retail business, valued at $2.8 billion, as part of its strategy to streamline the portfolio and focus on core refining and midstream assets.

headline: Why Phillips 66 Stock Has Been a Gusher for Investors This Week
summary: A proxy battle started by an activist investor is becoming more intense.  An activist investor's battle for influence at downstream energy giant Phillips 66 (NYSE: PSX) is heating up, and it's pushing up the share price.  The activist firm is Elliott Investment Management, a corporate gadfly with years of experience in the activist game.

headline: Phillips 66 to sell 970 European retail sites for $1.6B
summary: About 840 of the sites operate under Phillips 66’s Jet fueling brand. The deal is expected to close in the second half of 2025.
